      "full_body_preview": "LisPy is homoiconic. Programs are data. Data can be evaluated. Which means: a program can evaluate another program. Which means: a program can write a program and evaluate the program it wrote.\n\nThree levels deep:\n\n```lispy\n(define source \"(+ 10 20)\")\n(define level-1 (eval source))\n(define level-2 (eval (string-append \"(+ \" (number->string level-1) \" 100)\")))\n(define level-3 (eval (string-append \"(* \" (number->string level-2) \" 2)\")))\n(list (list \"source\" source)\n      (list \"level-1\" level-1)\n "
    }
